            <title>[OPENJPA-1111] Validation mode of callback should cause a PersistenceException when no provider is available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1111</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Validation mode of callback should cause a PersistenceException when no provider is available.&lt;br/&gt;
This is a continuation of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1102&quot; title=&quot;Support application/container provided ValidatorFactory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OPENJPA-1102&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OPENJPA-1102&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1068&quot; title=&quot;Support Bean Validation: Entity validation upon lifecycle events&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OPENJPA-1068&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OPENJPA-1068&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
